post_text: Invictus High School is back in session! Visit www.invictushighschool.org for more information on the Fall 2020 Semester, distance learning resources, and more! We can't wait to "see" you back at school!
text: Invictus High School is back in session! Visit www.invictushighschool.org for more information on the Fall 2020 Semester, distance learning resources, and more! We can't wait to "see" you back at school!

post_text:
The Spring 2020 semester has been challenging to each member of the Invictus High School family as we have all had to work together to come up with a new way to manage both personal and academic processes despite building closures.

We want to thank every member of our family-students, faculty, and staff-for their hard work and dedication to the completion of this academic year. We are grateful for each and every one of you.

Looking forward to seeing you all in the fall.

post_text:
Congratulations to the Class of 2020!

Invictus High School is so proud of all of our #undefeated graduates who pulled through the unanticipated building closure and still finished their high school journey strong. We are live-streaming our commencement event on 19 June, 2020 at 6:00 p.m. so that the Invictus High School Family and our community can gather virtually to send off our grads with the warmth and celebration worthy of their efforts.

Please join us at https://invictushigh.info/Channel at the below-listed date and time to celebrate with us.

post_text:
In light of recent events, Invictus High School is taking consideration of how we can support the mental health and wellness of our students. Especially at a time when our students are distanced from the faculty and staff members that they are accustomed to sounding off for advice and support, Invictus High School is taking steps to increase access to these key supports within our school community.

Our family advocates and and key supportive staff members have increased accessibility for students, which will be maintained vigilantly for the next couple of weeks. These available hours are for students to talk through whatever is on their mind, on top of our continued monitoring of email and online learning sessions for academics.

Visit https://invictushigh.info/Talk for details.

post_text:
Our students get individualized attention with a low student to teacher ratio.

During the unplanned building closure, we understand that the accessibility of our faculty and staff are key to making sure that students get the attention they need to succeed.

We have set up online learning sessions - virtual office hours where the faculty and staff you know are available via videoconferencing to answer questions, provide additional instruction, or just talk you through your day-to-day challenges.

Visit https://invictushigh.info/Virtual_Hours for a schedule of online learning sessions.

We know that it can be difficult to navigate education from home. The faculty and staff of Invictus High School remain dedicated to helping our students learn in this new learning environment.

If you're unsure how to contact your homeroom teacher or campus administrators, a good place to start is our all-staff directory, available at https://invictushigh.info/Directory

We can't wait to hear from you.
